            <a href="/nvc/Parachute.pptx" download style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Pitch Deck (PPTX)</a>
            <a href="/nvc/" style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--bg-soft); color: var(--fg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Full Summary</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SLIDE 1: The Race -->
    <section class="slide" style="padding-top: 6rem;">
        <div class="slide-label">The Landscape</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Everyone is racing to build<br>your AI agent.</h2>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p>OpenClaw. Claude Cowork. ZoComputer. Perplexity Computer. Manus. Over 100 million people already pay $20+/month for AI.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-row">
            <div class="stat">
                <div class="stat-num">$50B+</div>
                <div class="stat-label">Agentic AI market by 2030</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
                <div class="stat-num">44%</div>
                <div class="stat-label">CAGR</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.3rem; color: var(--fg);">Features get cloned in weeks. It&rsquo;s a race to the bottom. So we stopped trying to win it.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 2: The Problem -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">The Problem</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Memory is shallow.<br>Capture is broken.</h2>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p>These platforms all have memory now &mdash; but it&rsquo;s shallow. Basically one big text file. It remembers your name, not six months of your thinking. There&rsquo;s no structured knowledge about your projects, your people, your patterns over time.</p>
            <p>And there&rsquo;s a deeper problem upstream: <em>how</em> your thinking gets into the system. You can talk to your AI, but that&rsquo;s a conversation &mdash; the AI is always in the middle. There&rsquo;s no good way to just think for yourself, out loud, and have that become context.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p style="font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.3rem; color: var(--fg); margin-top: 1.5rem;">Tools that help us think for ourselves &mdash; not just think <em>with</em> AI &mdash; produce the quality of thinking that makes AI most useful.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 3: Parachute Daily -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Our Answer</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Parachute Daily.<br>Just talk.</h2>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p>A voice-first journal. Speak into a wearable pendant or your phone &mdash; on a walk, in the car, wherever thinking happens.</p>
            <p>Simple for humans. Native for AI. Your notes become structured data that any agent can work with &mdash; not locked inside one platform.</p>
            <p>No learning curve. No technical sophistication required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pendant-callout">
            <div class="label">The Pendant</div>
            <p>Wearable voice capture device. Go for a walk. Talk. Your thoughts become structured knowledge by the time you&rsquo;re home.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;"><strong style="color: var(--fg);">Working prototype on stage today.</strong></p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 4: Agent-Native Architecture -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Agent-Native</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Don&rsquo;t compete with agents.<br>Build the tool layer they all need.</h2>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p>Parachute is built on <strong>MCP</strong> (Model Context Protocol) &mdash; the open standard for connecting AI to tools. Your data lives in a graph database organized around three primitives: <strong>Things, Tags, and Tools.</strong></p>
            <p>Whatever AI you already use, Parachute makes it better. Connect your Parachute, and your AI can read your journals, search your notes, understand your context. You don&rsquo;t switch anything &mdash; you <em>add</em> Parachute.</p>
            <p>And because it&rsquo;s a graph database, your AI can do more than just read &mdash; it can <strong>create structure</strong>. It can scan your journals and generate people nodes, project nodes, link them, pull in contact info. Your notes become a living knowledge graph.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-diagram">
            <div class="arch-row">
                <span class="arch-label">you</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Parachute Daily</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Web &middot; Pendant &middot; Phone</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-arrow">&darr;</div>
            <div class="arch-row">
                <span class="arch-label">data</span>
                <span class="arch-box accent">Parachute Server &mdash; Things &middot; Tags &middot; Tools</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-arrow">&darr; MCP</div>
            <div class="arch-row">
                <span class="arch-label">agents</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Claude</span>
                <span class="arch-box">ChatGPT</span>
                <span class="arch-box">OpenClaw</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Any AI</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; font-family: var(--serif); color: var(--fg);">We&rsquo;re not trying to build the most intelligent tool. We&rsquo;re building the most important tool for intelligent systems to use.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 5: Context Compounds -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">The Insight</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Context compounds.</h2>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p>Every note, every voice entry builds a richer personal data layer &mdash; not a flat text file, but a real graph of your thinking that can be queried across months and years. That context is portable, it&rsquo;s yours, and no competitor can replicate it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flywheel">
            <div class="fw-step"><span class="fw-num">01</span> Capture thoughts in Daily</div>
            <div class="fw-step"><span class="fw-num">02</span> Build months of personal context</div>
            <div class="fw-step"><span class="fw-num">03</span> Connect any AI via MCP</div>
            <div class="fw-step"><span class="fw-num">04</span> AI already knows you</div>
            <div class="fw-step final"><span class="fw-num">&rarr;</span> Switching cost through genuine value</div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">Open source (AGPL-3.0). Local-first. Public Benefit Corporation. Your data is yours &mdash; portable, exportable, self-hostable. The trust required for people to share their deepest thinking.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 6: Business Model -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Business Model</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Start free.<br>Grow with every user.</h2>
        <div class="tier-table">
            <div class="tier-row">
                <div class="tier-price">Free</div>
                <div class="tier-body"><strong>Offline journal</strong> &mdash; on-device transcription, no sync. Zero hosting cost.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tier-row">
                <div class="tier-price">$2<span>/mo</span></div>
                <div class="tier-body"><strong>Cloud sync + MCP access</strong> &mdash; your notes across all devices, available to any AI agent</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tier-row">
                <div class="tier-price">$5<span>/mo</span></div>
                <div class="tier-body"><strong>Cloud transcription + cleanup</strong> &mdash; server-side processing, better accuracy</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tier-row tier-highlight">
                <div class="tier-price">$10<span>/mo</span></div>
                <div class="tier-body"><strong>AI reflections, vector search, and synthesis</strong> &mdash; your AI truly knows you.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="slide-body">
            <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">Free tier has zero hosting cost &mdash; no subsidizing free users. You&rsquo;re not asking anyone to switch AI tools. You&rsquo;re adding value wherever they already are.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SLIDE 7: Financial Projections -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Financial Projections</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Profitable by year three.</h2>
        <div class="fin-table">
